Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Pop them on a
large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{},
then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer. TIP: Use two #baking trays{} if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

While the wedges cook, pop the @British Hickory Smoked Sausages{2} onto another
baking tray.

Roast on the middle shelf of your oven until golden brown and cooked through,
~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. The sausages
> are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, lay in the @British Streaky Bacon{4%rashers} and fry until crispy and
brown, ~{3-4%minutes} on each side. Transfer to a #plate{} lined with
#kitchen paper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon
> thoroughly.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}. Quarter the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g}
and pop them into a #bowl{}.

Halve the @avocado{1} and remove the stone. Use a #tablespoon{} to scoop the
flesh out onto a #cutting board{}. Chop into 1cm pieces, then add to the bowl
of tomatoes and set aside.

Halve the @green chilli{1/2} lengthways, deseed, then finely chop. Grate the
@mature cheddar cheese{60%g}. Zest and halve the @lime{1}.

Pour enough @oil{} into the (now empty) frying pan to cover the bottom, then pop
it on medium heat.

Put the @plain flour{1}(see pantry for amount) into a small bowl and season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Separate the onion slices, add them to the flour and toss
to coat.

Once the oil is hot, add the onion and fry in batches until golden and crispy,
~{4-5%minutes}. Turn once or twice.

> TIP: Check if the oil is hot enough by adding one onion slice to the pan - if
> it sizzles, it's ready.

Transfer to some kitchen paper to absorb any excess oil.

When the wedges have 5 mins left, sprinkle over the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}
and return to the oven until melted, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Slice the @brioche hot dog buns{2} down through the middle (but not all the way
through) and pop into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add a squeeze of lime juice and a drizzle of @olive oil{} to avo and tomato bowl.
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then stir together.

In another small bowl, combine the @soured cream{75%g} with the lime zest and
season to taste.

When everything's ready, transfer the brioche buns to your plates.

Fill each bun with a sausage, 2 bacon rashers and a spoonful of zesty soured
cream. Sprinkle over the crispy onions and as much green chilli as you'd like
(careful, it's hot).

Serve the cheesy wedges and avocado salsa alongside with any remaining zesty
soured cream for dipping.

Enjoy!